race.comment: ELENA MONTERO (6) arrives fresh from an all-the-way win by a neck over this journey at Donald on December 2. Boasts a good record at the trip and horses with her profile tend to run well under this scenario. Plenty to like about her. CALAIS BLISS (9) pressed forward from a wide draw and fought hard to finish a narrow third here last start. No tougher this time, so she can take this out. DANCEENUFF (4) had their measure last time when getting the bob. Carries more weight now but is open to further improvement and deserves serious thought. BRIDIE'S LUCK (8) is desperate to break a long run of outs and is doing enough to suggest she can.
